35.ezboard.com/uthaldin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thaldin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 12:25:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 8th Coldain Ring War...</span><hr size=1> I was just wondering if anyone else was having problems with this.<br><br>I tried spawning it Friday night, killed the Ry'Gorr Chief, but Garadain never moved from his hut and dorfs never attacked the orcs &amp; giants.<br><br>GM gave me back my 7th ring, but said he couldn't do it again if I lost it again.  I was just wondering if it was a one time fluke and I should try again or if others have had this happen and I should wait? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiceisfun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IceIsFun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 4:53:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Coldain Ring War...</span><hr size=1> Spawning the 8th ring war:<br>1. Give your 7th ring to Garadain, receive marching orders.<br>2. Give marching orders to Gloradin Iceheart in the next hut (24hour spawn).<br>3. Kill the Ry'Gorr Chief, loot his head.<br>4. Give the head to the spawned Garadain.<br><br>I'm guessing you skipped step 2, which would prevent the orcs and dwarves from spawning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthaldin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thaldin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 5:50:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Coldain Ring War...</span><hr size=1> No, I did give the note to spawn the orcs and giants, and I did kill the RyGorr chief.<br><br>Garadain just never respawned up by the few dorfs that spawned, and never called charge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubloodshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bloodshard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 6:11:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Coldain Ring War...</span><hr size=1> Make sure you do not give the head to Garadain until he calls the charge. I don't know if you waited for that or not. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubloodshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bloodshard</A> at: 1/15/02 6:12:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxiggin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xiggin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 6:32:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Coldain Ring War...</span><hr size=1> The poster seemed to have done everything right...  However, there have been a few glitches with the Chief despawning and respawning as the quest version.<br><br>Sometimes, the original Chief will not despawn and you will see 2 Chiefs.  Under that scenario, you may have to kill both and Garadain may never leave his posts depending when the Chiefs were killed.    <br><br>It is hard to say what causes he glitch but the GM are very well aware of the problem.  The bad part is that usually they will leave all the giants up and the regular Orc crowd is screwed until the zone is repopped. At least, most GM will give back your 7th ring.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthaldin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thaldin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 6:36:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th Coldain Ring War...</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I even cleared out the inside of the orc fort before I spawned the war.<br><br>I'm just leary of retrying it because of the fact that if I lose my 7th ring to a bug a 2nd time, the GM said he won't be able to give me the ring again, and I really don't wanna do it all over. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urenbredesanea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Renbre Desanea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 11:37:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3819.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8th 